# EAS Update code-signing PRIVATE key material — must NEVER be committed. Only
# the PUBLIC certificate under certs/ is committed (embedded in the app). The
# private key signs updates and must live in a secrets manager / CI secret; a
# local copy used for signing is fine only while it stays untracked here. If a
# private key is ever committed or exposed, rotate it (new pair + new build).
keys/
